32:53.625 --> 32:55.667
I want to say something to you.

32:55.667 --> 32:57.500
I don't want you
to find it insulting.

32:57.500 --> 32:59.458
-Okay.
-There may have been a time

32:59.458 --> 33:02.208
when you understood the
psychological makeup of everyone

33:02.208 --> 33:04.375
in the company,
when you knew whom to assign

33:04.375 --> 33:07.291
any given task to in order
to achieve the desired result.

33:07.291 --> 33:09.000
I know how
my employees think.

33:09.000 --> 33:11.583
You're saying
I don't anymore?

33:11.583 --> 33:13.041
You don't anymore.

33:13.041 --> 33:14.375
Companies get bigger,

33:14.375 --> 33:15.917
modes of governance
and delegation need to change

33:15.917 --> 33:20.125
to keep pace, or...
you get this.

33:24.667 --> 33:26.667
It's not the best
short thesis on Klaxon,

33:26.667 --> 33:28.667
but I thought Ben Kim
could make it fly.

33:28.667 --> 33:30.417
He couldn't.
Mafee couldn't either.

33:30.417 --> 33:31.375
Their numbers dictate
it's a long,

33:31.375 --> 33:34.250
-so that's all they could see.
-Fuck me.

